claim: Recombinant technology leads to a broader immune response that may provide cross-protection, even in a mismatch season.
explanation: A table presenting vaccine effectiveness (VE) percentages (with 95% CI) for recombinant quadrivalent influenza vaccine (RIV4), standard-dose quadrivalent influenza vaccine (SD-IIV4), and RIV4 plus high-dose/adjuvanted influenza vaccines, compared with no vaccination, stratified by age groups (18–64 years and ≥65 years) and subgroups (overall, males, females). The table reports VE percentages for RIV4 and comparator vaccines against influenza, but it does not address broader immune responses, cross-protection, or effectiveness in mismatch seasons, and therefore does not support the claim. Note: Image is clear and complete for VE data, but contains no information on mismatch season performance or cross-protection.
